The paper discusses the design and optimization of communication networks, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also introduces a taxonomy for different algorithmic models, which suggests a focus on data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses objectives and evaluation metrics, which suggests a focus on information theory (cs.IT) and systems and control (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the inherent advantage of demand-aware networks over state-of-the-art demand-oblivious networks, which suggests a focus on algorithms (cs.AL).
